Private Lynndie England perhaps the most well-known in the abuse scandal that occurred in the fall of 2003 pleaded guilty to seven charges including two counts of conspiracy to maltreat prisoners four counts of maltreating prisoners and one count of committing an indecent act
Englands lawyers threw up their objections at the start of the court martial forcing a recess barely 30 minutes after the hearing opened and before England had made her expected guilty plea
The judge spent nearly three hours going over with England the details of an 11-page statement of facts that England acknowledged in her plea deal
